Class InkRecognitionUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.azure.cognitiveservices.inkrecognizer.model.InkRecognitionUnit
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    InkBullet, InkDrawing, InkList, InkWord, Line, Paragraph, WritingRegion

    public class InkRecognitionUnit
extends Object
    The InkRecognitionUnit class represents a single entity recognized by the InkRecognizer service.

    1.0
    Author:

        Returns:

      • children

        public Iterable<InkRecognitionUnit> children()
        The children of a model unit represent the units contained in a container unit An example is the relationship between a line and the words on the line. The words are the children of the line. "Leaf" units like words which have no children will always return an empty list.
        Returns:
        The children of the model unit

      • parent

        public InkRecognitionUnit parent()
        The parent of a model unit is the unit containing current unit. An example is the relationship between a line and the words on the line. The line is the parent of the words. A top level model unit will return null as the parent.
        Returns:
        The parent of the model unit

      • boundingBox

        public Rectangle boundingBox()
        The bounding box is the rectangular area that contains all the strokes in a model unit.
        Returns:
        The bounding rectangle

      • rotatedBoundingBox

        public Iterable<Point> rotatedBoundingBox()
        The rotated bounding box is the oriented rectangular area that contains all the strokes in a model unit. Its shape is influenced by the detected orientation of the ink in the model unit.
        Returns:
        The coordinate points of the rotated bounding rectangle.

      • id

        public long id()
        Returns unique identifier for the recognition unit.
        Returns:
        The identifier for the model unit.
